Culture Minister Dario Franceschini, who cut the ribbon to open the villa on Friday, said that while problems still remain at Pompeii, Italy is on schedule to meet their EU deadline.

Italy has been ordered to spend 105 million euros (£78million) in EU funds by the end of the year for maintenance and restoration projects, or lose its funding.

While only three projects have been completed, 13 are underway and some 65 million euros has been awarded in contracts, officials said. 

In addition, 85 people have been hired to work on the site and visitor numbers last year were 200,000 more than in 2013.

